ial and fascinating philosopher’s place in the history of Russian and Western thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aShestov, Lev,-1866-1938. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Individual Philosophers.2bisacsh  aBible.  aChekhov.  aContinental.  aDostoevsky.  aExistentialism.  aIbsen.  aIrrationalism.  aJewish thought.  aJudaism.  aKierkegaard.  aLev Shestov.  aMerezhkovskii.  aNietzsche.  aNihilism.  aRussian philosophy.  aShakespeare.  aSologub.  aTolstoy.  aTragic thought.  aTurgenev.  aliterature.  areligion.  atragedy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z97831106963010 cprintz978164469467140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644694688?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644694688423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644694688/original  a978-3-11-068820-7  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_BACKALL  a